    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of vegetable oil if the pan is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then chop your<strong> green beans</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong> and <strong>diced pepper</strong> to the<strong> </strong>mince and cook for 4-5 min further</p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>In a bowl combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, your <strong>red chilli relish</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong>, most of the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lime[s]</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until sticky and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>sticky sweet chilli mince</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-lean-pork-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sticky sweet chilli</strong> <strong>mince </strong>with <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>,<strong> remaining sliced spring onion </strong>and a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
